## How this project is structured

- Router test files: {{ tests_output }}/test_{tag}.py
- Service test stubs: {{ tests_output }}/test_{tag}_service.py
{% if services_output %}
- Service files: {{ services_output }}/{tag}.py
{% endif %}
- Factory helpers for building response objects: {{ tests_output }}/conftest.py
- Each test class maps to one API endpoint (documented in the class docstring)
{% if has_services %}

## The service mock pattern

Each test class has access to:
- `client_with_mock` — a TestClient with the service dependency overridden
- `mock_service` — an AsyncMock(spec={Tag}Service) wired into that client

The service method name is the snake_case operationId from the router (matches the
function name in {{ router_import_path | replace(".", "/") }}/{tag}/router.py).
{% endif %}

